"@EHAN":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/54f0fab1636872127e930300#post_54f0fab1636872127e930300
[bq="EHAN"]"@Shadow the Hedgehog":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/54f0f8486368720a52141900#post_54f0f8486368720a52141900
This is nothing new

Only weeks ago, the internet went crazy over Kim Kardashian's butt and nobody cared that we landed on a comet around the same time.[/bq]
Oh they cared about landing on the comet; except they hated it: look up #shirtgate

I know it's about drama, but I personally think the political correctness group/sjw/third wavers or such have reached the point in which they are objectively morally evil.  Why?  Cause the reason why they landed the satellite on the meteor was a proof of concept because it can in the long run prove that redirecting asteroids and such is possible thus theoretically saving every last human on the planet; even conservatively say mining asteroids can yield rare minerals and even tritium which would theoretically fix our global energy problem, provide a tens of trillions of dollars industry and provide tens of millions of people with high paying jobs and a liveable income.

I had several very heated arguments with these sorts of people during shirtgate and their entire points boiled down to "I don't care if every person on the planet dies; my feeling are more important".  In my book if someone believes that their personal feelings are more important than every last human life on the planet that makes them objectively a morally evil person.
